Query Optimization - Complete Notes
What is Query Optimization?
Query optimization is the process of improving the performance of a SQL query by reducing
execution time and resource usage.
Key Techniques
Use indexes, avoid SELECT *, use WHERE conditions, avoid functions on indexed columns, use
LIMIT, and prefer EXISTS over IN when appropriate.
Example (Bad vs Good)
Bad Query:
SELECT * FROM employees;
Optimized Query:
SELECT name, salary FROM employees WHERE department = 'IT';
Using Index
Creating an index to improve performance:
CREATE INDEX idx_dept ON employees(department);
Execution Plan
Use EXPLAIN and EXPLAIN ANALYZE to understand query performance.
EXPLAIN SELECT * FROM employees WHERE emp_id = 101;
EXPLAIN ANALYZE SELECT * FROM employees WHERE emp_id = 101;
